import { Grid } from '@material-ui/core';
import React from 'react';

function calc() {
	return (
		<Grid
			item
			container
			className="calc-cont"
			direction="column"
			alignItems="center"
			style={{ background: 'red' }}
		>
			<Grid container xs="10" item>
				<Grid item container style={{ background: 'green' }}>
					<Grid item xs="3">
						7
					</Grid>
					<Grid item>8</Grid>
					<Grid item>9</Grid>
					<Grid item>\</Grid>
				</Grid>
				<Grid item container style={{ background: 'grey' }}>
					<Grid item>4</Grid>
					<Grid item>5</Grid>
					<Grid item>6</Grid>
					<Grid item>x</Grid>
				</Grid>
				<Grid item container>
					<Grid item>1</Grid>
					<Grid item>2</Grid>
					<Grid item>3</Grid>
					<Grid item>-</Grid>
				</Grid>
				<Grid item container>
					<Grid item>0</Grid>
					<Grid item>.</Grid>
					<Grid item>=</Grid>
					<Grid item>+</Grid>
				</Grid>
			</Grid>
		</Grid>
	);
}

export default calc;
